Project 1 - Lexical Analyzer

========================================
REQUIREMENTS
========================================
Place ANTLR4.13.2 jar in project root.

========================================
HOW TO COMPILE AND RUN
========================================

Step 1: Generate lexer src from grammar
make generate

Step 2: Run a test file
make run FILE=test_programs/test1.c

Run all test programs at once:
make run-all

========================================
PROJECT FEATURES
========================================

1. Compound operators are matched before single-character operators
   LE ('<='), GE ('>='), EQ ('=='), NE ('!=') are defined before
   LT ('<'), GT ('>'), and ASSIGN ('=') in grammar.
   This assures that ANTLR doesn't accidentally tokenize '<=' as '<' and '='.

2. Keywords are defined before ID
   All 7 keywords (int, void, float, while, else, if, return) are defined
   before the ID rule. ANTLR matches rules in order, so keywords like
   'while' are never accidentally tokenized as identifiers.

3. Float literals follow spec
   FLOAT_NUM requires a decimal point and supports three forms:
   digits . digits 3.14
   digits . 1.
   . digits .1